{"title":"Técnicas de Diagnóstico Microbiológico-2024","guid":"","filepath":"/Users/criaah/Vault/📚 Resources/Mapas-Mentales/Entidades clínicas/General/Técnicas de Diagnóstico Microbiológico-2024.smmx","root":{"id":"0","parent":"-1","text":"- Técnicas de Diagnóstico\\NMicrobiológico","guid":"VMRHonPEPJBootHzfYbOqQ","children":[{"id":"1","parent":"0","text":"Microscopía y\\NTinciones","guid":"PQVbhBHo9btqo-0AMfKkpA","children":[{"id":"2","parent":"1","text":"Tinción de\\NGram","guid":"fyRsBH4I0XJpkJIkK3X7LA","children":[{"id":"3","parent":"2","text":"• Importancia: Diferencia bacterias en Gram positivas y Gram negativas.","guid":"Am6i9ETwGAMdSEqSGS7Qvw","children":[]},{"id":"4","parent":"2","text":"• Fundamento:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"5","parent":"4","text":"• Cristal violeta: Penetra la pared celular (Gram+ y Gram-).","guid":"NCg-WhYvsP01ueGSCN9MrQ","children":[]},{"id":"6","parent":"4","text":"• Yodo: Fija el cristal violeta formando complejo.","guid":"OzkV9nStGpA-8NS-M6hmlA","children":[]},{"id":"7","parent":"4","text":"• Alcohol-acetona:","guid":"GmyFRHbNr7lBDKIOYCTmAg","children":[{"id":"8","parent":"7","text":"• Gram+: Mantiene el cristal violeta (pared gruesa impide salida).","guid":"MX5cAlWwmIoKpgd6BkKjpA","children":[]},{"id":"9","parent":"7","text":"• Gram-: Se decolora (pared delgada, contenido lipídico permite escape).","guid":"SXTVGnNI2W4DyXJOQ-G0Gg","children":[]}]},{"id":"10","parent":"4","text":"• Safranina: Tinte de contraste (rojo para Gram-).","guid":"RHtl0VW9CERKOl_QAYDBVg","children":[]}]},{"id":"11","parent":"2","text":"Técnica","guid":"emzfAFEyjGNR85X2Blirtg","children":[{"id":"12","parent":"11","text":"Proceso:","guid":"eOuOGV3sb-c0md1IKmnqGw","children":[{"id":"13","parent":"12","text":"1. Cubre el frotis con cristal violeta (1 min).","guid":"YfQQIS-Ir8FOhJH3FhxOfA","children":[]},{"id":"14","parent":"12","text":"2. Lava con agua + solución de lugol (1 min) → Púrpura.","guid":"RbhgvgQ-c4ke-5spAPF2tA","children":[]},{"id":"15","parent":"12","text":"3. Decolora con alcohol-acetona + lava con agua → Gram+ (púrpura), Gram- (decolorado).","guid":"Moi-MDR2AA5A85GldwQkAg","children":[]},{"id":"16","parent":"12","text":"4. Añade safranina (1 min) → Gram+ (violeta), Gram- (rojo).","guid":"CjMIUgst8XZ4hOVYcdkGUQ","children":[]}]},{"id":"17","parent":"11","text":"Revela:","guid":"M50IcT8_5MIwrI3AfRHdiw","children":[{"id":"18","parent":"17","text":"• Afinidad tintorial:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"19","parent":"18","text":"• Gram+ → Violeta.","guid":"QAw-Ryv4S1JYo3BUcvNcig","children":[]},{"id":"20","parent":"18","text":"• Gram- → Rojo.","guid":"SPxDcWrj1YMoSR3CKvBTkg","children":[]}]}]}]},{"id":"21","parent":"2","text":"Permite conocer:","guid":"ewwjQ2AIPTdhFly2c_exXA","children":[{"id":"22","parent":"21","text":"• Forma bacteriana: Cocos, Bacilos, Cocobacilos, Vibrios, Espirilos, Espiroquetas.","guid":"PfStHxWwOf4eYZt4cZG1kA","children":[]},{"id":"23","parent":"21","text":"• Disposición bacteriana: Diplococos, Estreptococos, Micrococos, Sarcina, Estafilococos.","guid":"VPAewE8OKThuo5McB3jc8Q","children":[]}]},{"id":"24","parent":"2","text":"Utilidad clínica:","guid":"A4QpRi-XJMF-fQDzDbcxmA","children":[{"id":"25","parent":"24","text":"• Mínimo de bacterias detectables: 100,000 bacterias/mL.","guid":"OsUWN3cB5kt_kDfpetFUfg","children":[]},{"id":"26","parent":"24","text":"• Sensibilidad clínica\\Nsegún muestra:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"27","parent":"26","text":"• LCR: 75%.","guid":"IvoxnVgzqD1txLEJa_Z1Dg","children":[]},{"id":"28","parent":"26","text":"• Líquido pleural: 50-80%.","guid":"Qxd9wBYNzssW5sihXYQDBA","children":[]},{"id":"29","parent":"26","text":"• Líquido peritoneal: 25-50%.","guid":"DNt-hVfzaq89qOkGB-ehyA","children":[]},{"id":"30","parent":"26","text":"• Líquido articular: 50%.","guid":"N_un5x6_Rbx731MkdfBVBg","children":[]},{"id":"31","parent":"26","text":"• Orina: Se correlaciona con urocultivo positivo.","guid":"NG9_uhpA7pxnggqWCV-eeg","children":[]}]}]}]},{"id":"32","parent":"1","text":"Tinción de\\NCápsula","guid":"SYyDhg4MUvs4sL37EsPSHA","children":[{"id":"33","parent":"32","text":"Utilidad:","guid":"BldiqXoaqps7Uy0qKVGURw","children":[{"id":"34","parent":"33","text":"• Evidencia la cápsula microbiana (↗️ virulencia).","guid":"aU8X1FYlnbIQ2HtrbNNBGg","children":[]}]},{"id":"35","parent":"32","text":"• Usa tinta china (no tiñe cápsula, resto del microorganismo se tiñe con safranina).","guid":"BbzCdA9VfF56inKyQIHYqw","children":[]}]},{"id":"36","parent":"1","text":"Tinción de\\NEsporas","guid":"aVxJqlAdVWAvXUcvKV2Cow","children":[{"id":"37","parent":"36","text":"Utilidad:","guid":"Uk5S2CkX3jMVSAlVFWXQmA","children":[{"id":"38","parent":"37","text":"• Identifica esporas (↗️ resistencia).","guid":"PyWs_iwu0fZy6dOcTAErgw","children":[]}]},{"id":"39","parent":"36","text":"• Usando verde de malaquita (tiñe esporas, resto con safranina).","guid":"BCI8pjCSvKJT6M1LPB3kjQ","children":[]},{"id":"40","parent":"36","text":"• Ej: Bacillus.","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"41","parent":"1","text":"Tinción de\\NZiehl-Neelsen","guid":"bl01VlntzVMqlvSFDMwf7w","children":[{"id":"42","parent":"41","text":"Importancia:","guid":"T1ICXk_IIHAyDjmTA8GCGA","children":[{"id":"43","parent":"42","text":"• Detecta bacilos ácido-alcohol resistentes (BAAR), e.g., Mycobacterium tuberculosis.","guid":"agkPDBmQRCkNISCTU1gm4Q","children":[]}]},{"id":"44","parent":"41","text":"Fundamento:","guid":"b7Xh3B35m_5AK2f7dXKkUA","children":[{"id":"45","parent":"44","text":"• Fucsina + ácido micólico → Complejo resistente al alcohol-clorhídrico → Fucsia (BAAR), Azul de metileno (resto).","guid":"LU8YXTq12q419Hz7M6Z7Bg","children":[]}]},{"id":"46","parent":"41","text":"Técnica:","guid":"NNCFSXFHqiVc-A9NBx7YIg","children":[{"id":"47","parent":"46","text":"1. Frotis con fucsina Ziehl-Neelsen.","guid":"Gl-IWHJAGKMchKi6WYU1Vw","children":[]},{"id":"48","parent":"46","text":"2. Exponer a vapor (2-3 min).","guid":"Hm7qmQ9ufFclhmDaIpEnPw","children":[]},{"id":"49","parent":"46","text":"3. Decolorar con alcohol-ácido.","guid":"QAE4-XlvLiZerwvMD1M7WA","children":[]},{"id":"50","parent":"46","text":"4. Contrastar con azul de metileno (30 seg).","guid":"STdOlhC9RV8TFL1wM0Bdog","children":[]}]},{"id":"51","parent":"41","text":"Utilidad\\NClínica:","guid":"Kk2JiSA13gMGmISDGgNrZQ","children":[{"id":"52","parent":"51","text":"• Diagnóstico de tuberculosis (bacilos BAAR).","guid":"Pi96AkbD7H8Pdg-1a36SXw","children":[]},{"id":"53","parent":"51","text":"• Sensibilidad varía según muestra (LCR: 75%, orina: correlación con cultivo positivo).","guid":"AXnHLUVqjLAfJQ1lNkpMdg","children":[]},{"id":"54","parent":"51","text":"• Cantidad mínima detectable: 5, 000 a 10,000 bacilos/mL.","guid":"NrI21nwdHLM9aSSYURG_Lg","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"55","parent":"1","text":"Tinción con\\NAnaranjado de\\NAcridina","guid":"HsmYW0vFe2xGBC--SRch5A","children":[{"id":"56","parent":"55","text":"Utilidad:","guid":"N_sprjTOczZLJLRkbq1ghA","children":[{"id":"57","parent":"56","text":"• Tiñe ADN bacteriano (naranja) y ADN humano (verde/amarillo).","guid":"a_tZb0yctEJjGo1JKirTcQ","children":[]},{"id":"58","parent":"56","text":"• Alta sensibilidad para microscopía de bacterias (↗️fluorescencia).","guid":"E2CgwXKQnP4VqWXQFNpn7g","children":[]}]},{"id":"59","parent":"55","text":"• Ejemplo: Bartonella henselae.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"60","parent":"55","text":"• Indica presencia bacteriana → Realizar Tinción de Gram.","guid":"MOuP6QiN2P0_vx-zH0jFPw","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"61","parent":"0","text":"Cultivos","guid":"OnNpmFtyLF11NXKdA__tHg","children":[{"id":"62","parent":"61","text":"1. Importancia:","guid":"YnumUGpWFDgsFOUuS9fv-g","children":[{"id":"63","parent":"62","text":"• Técnica de referencia en microbiología clínica.","guid":"aX5_WS3mMJkWw786CEgXtA","children":[]},{"id":"64","parent":"62","text":"• Identifica agentes etiológicos y realiza estudios de sensibilidad a antimicrobianos.","guid":"eausBVzH7vlRXzmYZacFdA","children":[]},{"id":"65","parent":"62","text":"• Detecta microorganismos vivos.","guid":"KWSjOzR5xuEP0djmPMVD_A","children":[]},{"id":"66","parent":"62","text":"• Indicador clave: crecimiento bacteriano ↔️ diagnóstico correcto.","guid":"Jwpj3yV7PrZRn6vqXwWNjQ","children":[]}]},{"id":"67","parent":"61","text":"2. Medios de\\Ncultivo:","guid":"cxlY4UI5Cbt-UOa5Ow-d6A","children":[{"id":"68","parent":"67","text":"• Estado físico: Sólidos, Líquidos, Semi-sólidos.","guid":"JVI5Sw1yDcUqfgcUB83fmw","children":[]},{"id":"69","parent":"67","text":"• Presentación: En placa, En tubo.","guid":"d8gh_VaS7ENTpc-VMjuLlg","children":[]},{"id":"70","parent":"67","text":"• Contenido de nutrientes: Comunes, Enriquecidos.","guid":"MgUYoEjbQjM2O3i0G4OX-Q","children":[]},{"id":"71","parent":"67","text":"• Utilidad: Aislamiento primario, Selectivos, Diferenciales, Pruebas bioquímicas.","guid":"dsFyzEz_N-8jy6-tcG0e0Q","children":[]},{"id":"72","parent":"67","text":"Tipos","guid":"","children":[{"id":"73","parent":"72","text":"1. Medios\\NEnriquecidos:","guid":"aGmIInP-Vg0NW76-WlqrHQ","children":[{"id":"74","parent":"73","text":"• Agar sangre (AS): Diferencia tipos de hemólisis.","guid":"Kccm6HUq6UVWFCRFUyvKIw","children":[]},{"id":"75","parent":"73","text":"• Agar chocolate (AC): Favorece crecimiento de organismos fastidiosos (e.g., Neisseria, Haemophilus).","guid":"KaSwJmXl_SsP8Q4fUK8UBQ","children":[]}]},{"id":"76","parent":"72","text":"2. Medios\\NSelectivos/Diferenciales:","guid":"flUaV31nj6Vw4C-kI6dTow","children":[{"id":"77","parent":"76","text":"• MacConkey (Mac): Selecciona Gram- y diferencia fermentadores de lactosa.","guid":"C2E74mGQugkvtKGTZartzg","children":[]},{"id":"78","parent":"76","text":"• Agar sal manitol (AS): Selecciona Staphylococcus aureus (fermenta manitol → amarillo).","guid":"CtmdahteNrgrdTM-AqG_Zw","children":[]},{"id":"79","parent":"76","text":"• Agar eosina-azul de metileno (AME): Selecciona Enterobacteriaceae (fermentadores de lactosa → azul/negro).","guid":"cfEi-38bAtQ03Ur9I_Y7nA","children":[]}]},{"id":"80","parent":"72","text":"3. Medios para Aislamiento\\Nde Anaerobios:","guid":"R_ZFB2sYw7I_edOVPre30w","children":[{"id":"81","parent":"80","text":"• Caldo de tioglicolato (CFT): Aísla anaerobios.","guid":"OBf7oWNFg0MvJNakYd8iiQ","children":[]},{"id":"82","parent":"80","text":"• Agar de Wilkins y Chalgren (WC): Aísla anaerobios estrictos.","guid":"WHBsiAU4-uk1CuysAhUcrw","children":[]}]},{"id":"83","parent":"72","text":"4. Medios Especiales para\\NGrupos Particulares:","guid":"ax74FUT7-stSxDC0doAz9w","children":[{"id":"84","parent":"83","text":"• Agar Sabouraud: Favorece crecimiento de hongos.","guid":"Joy01AJ40kdcKyHFJOHPKw","children":[]},{"id":"85","parent":"83","text":"• Agar Lowenstein Jensen (LJ): Aísla Mycobacterium tuberculosis.","guid":"f-Bh7E0LUWlIiSLOCrn_Vg","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"86","parent":"67","text":"Técnicas de Siembra\\NMicrobiológica","guid":"LVHNbT3Kuk95x1W7ZWnJDg","children":[{"id":"87","parent":"86","text":"1. Siembra en placas:","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"88","parent":"86","text":"• Siembra en cuadrantes:\\NGenera colonias aisladas.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"89","parent":"86","text":"• Siembra directa (tórula): Se siembra\\Ndirectamente sobre el medio.","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"90","parent":"67","text":"Técnicas de Siembra y Métodos de\\NIdentificación Bacteriana","guid":"IRA9kijsLF9HSOuXeYCqGg","children":[{"id":"91","parent":"90","text":"1. Técnicas de\\NSiembra en Placas:","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"92","parent":"90","text":"• Siembra en cuadrantes:","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"93","parent":"90","text":"• Objetivo: Obtener\\Ncolonias aisladas.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"94","parent":"90","text":"• Método: Uso de asa en\\Nzonas consecutivas.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"95","parent":"90","text":"• Siembra cuantitativa\\N(asa calibrada):","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"96","parent":"90","text":"• Objetivo: Cuantificar\\Nbacterias en una muestra.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"97","parent":"90","text":"• Método: Inoculación de 1 µL en\\Nlínea vertical, luego estriado.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"98","parent":"90","text":"2. Métodos para\\NIdentificación Bacteriana:","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"99","parent":"90","text":"• Post-incubación\\N(16-24 hrs a 37°C):","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"100","parent":"90","text":"• Observación de\\Ncrecimiento bacteriano.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"101","parent":"90","text":"• Identificación:","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"102","parent":"90","text":"• Macroscópica: Descripción de colonias\\N(tamaño, forma, elevación, margen, color,\\Naspecto, densidad, consistencia).","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"103","parent":"90","text":"• Bioquímica: Diferenciación por\\Nreacciones metabólicas (e.g., catalasa,\\Nureasa, oxidasa, coagulasa).","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"104","parent":"67","text":"Descripción\\NMacroscópica de\\NColonias:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"105","parent":"104","text":"• Tamaño: Grande (>1 mm), Mediano\\N(≈1 mm), Pequeño (<1 mm).","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"106","parent":"104","text":"• Forma: Circular, Filamentosa, Irregular,\\NPuntiforme, Rizode, Ovalada.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"107","parent":"104","text":"• Elevación: Plana, Elevada, Convexa,\\NRedonda, Centro elevado, Umbilicada.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"108","parent":"104","text":"• Margen: Entera, Ondulada, Lobulada,\\NDentada, Filamentosa, Rizada.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"109","parent":"104","text":"• Color: Blanco, Negro,\\NCrema, Naranja, etc.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"110","parent":"104","text":"• Apariencia de Superficie:\\NBrillante, Rugosa, Cremosa.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"111","parent":"104","text":"• Translucidez: Opaca,\\NTransparente, Translúcida.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"112","parent":"104","text":"• Consistencia:\\NFriable, Membranosa.","guid":"","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"113","parent":"61","text":"Identificación\\NBioquímica de\\NBacterias","guid":"LiUnSHxT2EN7lcbJGUQfXQ","children":[{"id":"114","parent":"113","text":"1. Métodos Clásicos:","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"115","parent":"113","text":"• Uso de batería de tubos con\\Ninoculación manual.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"116","parent":"113","text":"• Identificación basada en\\Npruebas bioquímicas:","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"117","parent":"113","text":"• Pruebas clave: Catalasa, Oxidasa, Fermentación\\Nde glucosa, Producción de gas, Descarboxilación\\Nde aminoácidos, entre otros.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"118","parent":"113","text":"2. Sistemas Automatizados:","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"119","parent":"113","text":"• Uso de medios comerciales en\\Nsistemas automatizados.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"120","parent":"113","text":"• Ventajas:","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"121","parent":"113","text":"• Rapidez:\\NIdentificación más\\Nrápida.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"122","parent":"113","text":"• Menor costo: Menos\\Nlaborioso y más eficiente.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"123","parent":"113","text":"• Mayor confiabilidad: Menor margen de error\\Ncon más pruebas simultáneas.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"124","parent":"113","text":"3. Ejemplos Visuales:","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"125","parent":"113","text":"• Fig. 17: Identificación bioquímica de\\Nbacterias Gram- de relevancia médica.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"126","parent":"113","text":"• Fig. 18 y 19: Sistemas automatizados para\\Nidentificación bacteriana (e.g., Proteus vulgaris\\NATCC 13315 con baterías comerciales).","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"127","parent":"61","text":"Detección de Antígenos y\\NProductos Bacterianos","guid":"QU_TDk5Z934PxFNUZ9yH4g","children":[{"id":"128","parent":"127","text":"1. Test Rápidos:","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"129","parent":"127","text":"• Streptococcus pneumoniae: Test de látex\\N(LCR, líquido pleural, esputo, orina).","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"130","parent":"127","text":"• Neisseria meningitidis:\\NTest de látex (LCR).","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"131","parent":"127","text":"• Haemophilus influenzae tipo\\Nb: Test de látex (LCR).","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"132","parent":"127","text":"• Streptococcus pyogenes (Grupo A):\\NInmunofluorescencia (Aspirado o hisopado faríngeo).","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"133","parent":"127","text":"• Mycobacterium tuberculosis: ADA (adenosina\\Ndeaminasa) en LCR y líquido pleural.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"134","parent":"127","text":"• Helicobacter pylori: Ureasa\\Nen biopsia gástrica.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"135","parent":"127","text":"2. Detección de\\NÁcidos Nucleicos:","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"136","parent":"127","text":"• Mediante Hibridación:","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"137","parent":"127","text":"• Directa en muestra: Detecta Streptococcus,\\NLegionella pneumophila, Chlamydia\\Ntrachomatis, Neisseria gonorrhoeae.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"138","parent":"127","text":"• Confirmación de cultivo: Detecta Enterococcus,\\NStreptococcus spp., Haemophilus influenzae, Listeria\\Nmonocytogenes, Mycobacterium tuberculosis.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"139","parent":"127","text":"• Mediante PCR (Amplificación\\Nde Ácidos Nucleicos):","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"140","parent":"127","text":"• Detecta una variedad creciente de bacterias\\Ncon alta precisión y rapidez, complementando\\Ntécnicas convencionales.","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"141","parent":"61","text":"Cito-histopatología","guid":"UNLJxWvvdRoMvlcOULMrsg","children":[{"id":"142","parent":"141","text":"1. Citología:","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"143","parent":"141","text":"• Muestras: Secreciones (esputo), fluidos corporales (LCR,\\Nlíquidos articulares, pleural), lavados o cepillados\\Nendoscópicos, tejidos obtenidos por punción.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"144","parent":"141","text":"• Utilidad: Observación microscópica directa para el\\Ndiagnóstico de infecciones bacterianas.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"145","parent":"141","text":"2. Histología:","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"146","parent":"141","text":"• Muestras: Tejidos obtenidos\\Npor biopsia o autopsia.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"147","parent":"141","text":"• Utilidad: Estudio histopatológico para la observación de\\Nrespuesta tisular y diagnóstico de infecciones crónicas,\\Ninflamatorias, y granulomatosas (e.g., Mycobacterium\\Ntuberculosis, Bartonella henselae).","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"148","parent":"141","text":"• Tinciones utilizadas: Tinción de\\NGram y Warthin-Starry.","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"149","parent":"61","text":"Detección de Anticuerpos\\NEspecíficos (Serología)","guid":"","children":[{"id":"150","parent":"149","text":"1. Principios:","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"151","parent":"149","text":"• Detecta anticuerpos específicos (IgM, IgG) en\\Nrespuesta a infecciones bacterianas.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"152","parent":"149","text":"• IgM: Indicador de\\Ninfección reciente.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"153","parent":"149","text":"• IgG: Indicador de infección\\Npasada o exposición previa.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"154","parent":"149","text":"2. Aplicaciones:","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"155","parent":"149","text":"• Diagnóstico indirecto de infecciones cuando\\Notros métodos no son viables.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"156","parent":"149","text":"• Utilización de técnicas como fijación de\\Ncomplemento e inhibición de hemaglutinación\\Npara la detección en suero.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"157","parent":"149","text":"3. Ventajas/Desventajas:","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"158","parent":"149","text":"• Ventajas:\\NSencillez y bajo\\Ncosto.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"159","parent":"149","text":"• Desventajas: Posibilidad de reacciones\\Ncruzadas y menor especificidad.","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"160","parent":"61","text":"Técnicas de Detección de\\NAnticuerpos en Suero","guid":"OPrGg1VHedxbbSsIIWROpQ","children":[{"id":"161","parent":"160","text":"1. Pruebas Rápidas y Tipos de\\NAnticuerpos Detectados:","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"162","parent":"160","text":"• Mycoplasma: IFI, ELISA → IgM, IgG (Suero).","guid":"SUXP6WjI6cZ7vvnDPF8oyg","children":[]},{"id":"163","parent":"160","text":"• Legionella: IFI → IgG (Suero).","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"164","parent":"160","text":"• Treponema pallidum: MHA, ELISA, FTA-Abs,\\NVDRL, RPR → IgM, IgG (Suero).","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"165","parent":"160","text":"• Salmonella Typhi: Aglutinación en placa,\\NELISA → IgM + IgG (Suero).","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"166","parent":"160","text":"• Leptospira: Aglutinación en tubo\\N→ IgM + IgG (Suero).","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"167","parent":"160","text":"• Bartonella sp: IFI →\\NIgM, IgG (Suero).","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"168","parent":"160","text":"• Mycobacterium tuberculosis: ELISA\\N→ IgM, IgG, IgA (Suero).","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"169","parent":"160","text":"• Brucella sp: Aglutinación en tubo\\N→ IgM + IgG (Suero).","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"170","parent":"160","text":"• Chlamydia pneumoniae:\\NIFI → IgG (Suero).","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"171","parent":"160","text":"• Borrelia burgdorferii: ELISA, IFI,\\NWestern blot → IgM (Suero).","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"172","parent":"160","text":"2. Métodos Utilizados:","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"173","parent":"160","text":"• Neutralización.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"174","parent":"160","text":"• Inmunofluorescencia (IFI).","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"175","parent":"160","text":"• Aglutinación del látex.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"176","parent":"160","text":"• Inmunoanálisis\\Nenzimático (ELISA).","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"177","parent":"160","text":"• Radioinmunoensayo.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"178","parent":"160","text":"• Western blot.","guid":"","children":[]}]}]}]},"node_count":178,"relations":[],"cross_references":[],"specialty":"General","folder":"Entidades clínicas/General","filename":"Técnicas de Diagnóstico Microbiológico-2024","id":"map_877","resolved_references":[]}